MOMO The Raccoon
Well, shit. My latest photoset kinda exploded because of the raccoon omg. Long story short, I discovered that Skyrim Wildlife Overhaul had a raccoon in it, didnt wanted the rest so I only sneaked the lil fella out of the mod, and created a standalone animal follower out of it. Hope you all enjoy Momo!

MOD DESCRIPTION
Momo is an essential Raccoon animal follower mod, with its own custom dialogues. Momo has the muffled movement, light foot and stealth perks, he also will carry your burdens if youre over loaded. Momo will be level 10 when you first encounter him and will level up with the player till 100.

Keep in mind that Momo is build around my gameplay, so he might be a lil bit overpowered if you play on any mode thats below Legendary-Expert.

  • WHERE TO FIND MOMO
Clearpine Pond
  • REQUIREMENTS

Latest version of skyrim.
Hearthfires

  • INSTALLING

Install it either manually or with NMM.
Choice is yours.

  • CREDITS

530gothic25 for the raccoon mesh & texture.

  • || D O W N L O A D ||

Looking for CNHF BETA testers

People had been requesting me this one thing for a super long time, and I crazily have decided to freaking do it.

Making vanilla conversions for the CNHF barbarian body, yes, with weight sliders! Im trying to make the Barbarian variant completely standalone, so you wouldnt have to download the 2_0 anymore. Not only am I doing this because of the crazy amount of request, but also because every time I end up at the CNHF nexus pages, I cry and die a little when I read the comments. Like most people said there, CNHF IS a gem and it is sad to see it being silence now. I wont allow it to succumb it to oblivion, as nexus user hirsepimpel said it.

However, I will try to move CNHF forward, but not 2_0 or the vanilla one, but the Barbarian one of course, since all the stuff I ever do is for that body, because love. ANYHOW Back to the reason of this post.

Being a single mom, student and a security worker, it is HARD to do EVERYTHING on my own. To help me gain more spare time to pull this insane stunt out, I am seeking out BETA testers. A group of people who have the time and are willingly to help me test out the armor conversions. When I say testing, I dont mean put on the armor and run around with it, no. Some real good ol fashion testing, putting it on, running, jumping, combat, checking it with different poses, clippings, you name it. Hell, make a new save file just for this, and play the game a little bit.

I am also planning to do this replacer differently than most body mods. I will make it dependable with an esp, so it wont replace any armors of bodies people have currently installed. Example, if you decide you want to use CNHF, just active the esp and once you wish to go back to whatever default shit you were using, just simply disable the esp.

Now thats all said, if youre interested to help me with this, please message me here! Preferable with the new chat system. Hell, if you know your way with either 3dsmax or blender and want to help with the armors part, dont hesitate to join in, its all hands on deck!

And if you want to but cannot help with any of this, then please reblog this post, so maybe someone out there can and will.

Cheers!

OVERWATCH
D.Va

I play to win.

D.Va is a former professional gamer who now uses her skills to pilot a state-of-the-art mech in defense of her homeland.

Twenty years ago, South Korea was attacked by a colossal omnic monstrosity that rose from the depths of the East China Sea. The massive, lumbering construct caused catastrophic damage to coastal cities before it was driven back beneath the waves. In response, the South Korean government developed a mechanized armored drone unit, called MEKA, to protect urban environments in future engagements with the omnic threat.

The governments fears proved to be well founded, as a disturbing pattern of attacks emerged. Every few years, the monstrosity would rise from the sea to assault South Korea and its neighbors. The omnic learned from these encounters, often reconfiguring itself in a different form and appearing with new weapons and capabilities. Each incident ended in a stalemate, with the monstrosity defeated but not destroyed.

As the omnic continued to adapt, it eventually disrupted MEKAs drone-control networks, forcing the military to place pilots in the mechs. Scrambling to find suitable candidates, the government turned to the countrys professional gamers, who possessed the necessary reflexes and instincts to operate the mechs advanced weapons systems. Top stars were drafted, including reigning world champion Hana Song, also known as D.Va. Famous for her elite skills, D.Va was a fierce competitor who played to win at all costs, and she had a well-earned reputation for showing no mercy to her opponents.

Seeing her new mission as a game, D.Va fearlessly charges into battle alongside the rest of her MEKA unit, ready to spring to her nations defense at a moments notice. Recently, she has begun to stream combat operations to her adoring fans, and her growing following has turned her into a global icon.
